[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Global redzone:          f9[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Poisoned by user:        f7[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Container overflow:      fc[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Array cookie:            ac[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Intra object redzone:    bb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ASan internal:           fe[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Left alloca redzone:     ca[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpo3fjz960[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was detected in the Mongoose codebase [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring a libFuzzer run. The overflow occurs in the function `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing a fuzzed ICMP packet. A single-byte read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis performed just past the end of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap allocation, leading to an [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds access.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During fuzz testing, AddressSanitizer flagged a one-byte read beyond the end of a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap buffer in `rx_icmp`. The call stack shows the overflow propagating from [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rx_icmp` into `mg_tcpip_rx`, and then into the fuzz harness entry point [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `test/fuzz.c`.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Heap-based buffer overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mout-of-bounds read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. ASan classifies this as a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“heap-buffer-overflow” with “SCARINESS: [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m.”[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important Observations and Findings  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The faulty read occurs at offset [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte allocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39maddress [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0x504000000150[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The allocation is performed in the fuzz harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:95[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhappens in production code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The sanitized log shows the redzone immediately after the allocated region, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming the one-byte overrun.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The functions in the trace:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `mg_tcpip_rx` at net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:897[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    – `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` at test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:106[0m[39m  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **rx_icmp [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnet_builtin.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Boundary checks on ICMP header and payload lengths.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Index calculations used when reading packet bytes.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **mg_tcpip_rx [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnet_builtin.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – How packet buffers are handed off to ICMP processing.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Any upstream size validations.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Fuzz Harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtest/fuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Allocation size and initialization of packet data passed to `mg_tcpip_rx`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Ensuring that the harness does not artificially restrict buffer size in ways[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat mask real-world traffic patterns.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. **pkt Structure Definitions**  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Definitions of packet metadata [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlength fields, offsets[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Interaction between pkt length and actual allocated buffer.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mExamining these components together will provide a holistic view of how packet data[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis validated [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor not[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before ICMP processing and where the buffer overflow boundary[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck is missing.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpo3fjz960[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing run of the Mongoose networking code uncovered a one‐byte [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap‐buffer‐overflow in the function `rx_icmp` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfile `src/net_builtin.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash occurs when processing ICMP echo requests, reading past the end of the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated `pkt->raw.buf` region. An attempted patch adds calculations to clamp the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mICMP payload length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`plen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to both the transmit buffer capacity [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`space`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremaining bytes in the raw packet [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`avail`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but re-running the fuzzer shows the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame AddressSanitizer overflow in `rx_icmp` at the same source location.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer’s AddressSanitizer log reports a heap-buffer-overflow at `rx_icmp` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m in `net_builtin.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m during a read of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The overflow address [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x5040[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m0172[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is exactly one byte past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x5040[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m0150[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x5040[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m0172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m made in the fuzzer harness [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The backtrace shows the error arises on the path: `rx_icmp` → `mg_tcpip_rx` → [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz entry point. No other parts of the codebase are implicated.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The bug triggers only when handling ICMP type [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mecho request[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and when the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpacket payload buffer is too small.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The raw packet buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->raw.buf` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `pkt->raw.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is allocated based on [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer input size; the ICMP payload pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->pay.buf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m may point near the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer end.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The code computes `hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39meth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and then [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`space = ifp->tx.len - hlen`. It later uses `pkt->pay.len` unbounded by the actual [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable bytes in `pkt->raw.buf`.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch breaks the long `hlen` expression into multiple lines.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It computes an offset of the payload within the raw buffer:  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  size_t offset = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->pay.buf - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->raw.buf[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  size_t avail  = pkt->raw.len > offset ? pkt->raw.len - offset : [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- It then clamps `plen` to both the transmit buffer capacity [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`space`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and this new[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`avail` value:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```c[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  plen = space;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > avail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  plen = avail;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After clamping, it proceeds to build the ICMP echo reply.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Re-running the fuzzer with the patched code produces the identical overflow [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreport at the same source line in `rx_icmp`. The crash address, stack trace, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation region remain unchanged.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The entirety of `rx_icmp` in `net_builtin.c`, especially how it reads from [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->pay.buf` and how `pkt->raw.len` [0m[35m/[0m[39m `pkt->pay.len` are initially set.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The parsing logic that sets `pkt->pay.buf` and `pkt->pay.len` in the packet [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreception code [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_tcpip_rx`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or earlier routines.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any related length checks in the IPv4 header parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., verifying `ip->hlen` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst `pkt->raw.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the boundary between header and payload.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interaction between `[0m[1;35mtx_ip[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` parameters [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreply size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the actual memory [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable for reply data.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA more holistic review of packet‐buffer management—covering both receive‐side [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing and transmit‐side buffer allocation—will be needed to understand why a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone‐byte read past the buffer boundary still occurs after clamping.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report revealed a one-byte heap buffer overflow in the function[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rx_icmp` within `src/net_builtin.c` when processing a fuzzed packet. An attempted [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch added boundary checks and pointer‐offset calculations to prevent [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds reads, including verifying the raw packet buffer length, clamping the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpayload length, and guarding against invalid offsets. However, after applying the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch, the same heap‐buffer‐overflow error persists at the same source location.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer log shows a heap‐buffer‐overflow at `net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385:18[0m[39m` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is a single‐byte read past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte allocated region.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The offending read occurs when accessing memory at `pkt->pay.buf` without [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msufficient validation of the underlying `pkt->raw` buffer.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerable code path is triggered by the fuzzer’s call to [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, which constructs and passes arbitrary packet data into [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_tcpip_rx`.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The Fuzzer runs with a small allocated packet [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`malloc` size [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->pay.buf` is computed relative to `pkt->raw.buf`.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No prior checks ensure that `pkt->raw.len` is large enough to cover both [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheaders and the payload region.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is consistently reproducible with different seeds, indicating [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsufficient guarding in `rx_icmp` rather than a one-off memory layout issue.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added standard headers for `memcpy`, `memset`, and `ptrdiff_t`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Computed a minimal header size `hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39meth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Early return if `pkt->raw.len` is smaller than `hlen`.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Filtered non-echo ICMP packets and non-destined packets before further [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprocessing.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calculated `offset = pkt->pay.buf - pkt->raw.buf` and returned if the payload [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion falls outside `pkt->raw.len`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clamped the requested payload copy length to the transmit buffer capacity [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ifp->tx.len - hlen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Rebuilt the ICMP echo reply with zeroed header, copied the validated payload, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand recalculated the checksum.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer still reports a heap‐buffer‐overflow at the same line in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rx_icmp`.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow remains a one-byte read past the end of the allocated region.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This suggests that one or more of the newly added checks do not fully cover [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mall malformed packet layouts that exercise the vulnerable read.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Further Investigation  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine how `pkt->pay.buf` and `pkt->raw.buf` are initialized and whether [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->pay.len` can exceed the remaining raw buffer space under any condition not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcovered by the patch.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review upstream parsing in `mg_tcpip_rx` to ensure correct setting of [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->raw.len`, `pkt->pay.buf`, and related fields before calling `rx_icmp`.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Investigate other code paths in `rx_icmp` that may index into packet data [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., IP header options, variable-length headers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and whether they need similar [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Audit usage of pointer arithmetic on packed network headers to confirm [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malignment and size assumptions hold for all packet variants.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer report shows an AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow in function [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`rx_icmp` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, triggered when processing a malformed ICMP packet. A[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch was applied to add header‐length checks, IHL validation, payload‐offset [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checking, and early returns before copying or reading data. Despite these [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguards, the same overflow error recurs at the same location in `rx_icmp`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A one‐byte heap‐buffer‐overflow is reported in `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The crash occurs reading past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m‐byte heap allocation [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x504000000150[0m[39m`–`[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when accessing packet data.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer log shows the overflow happens during `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and down in the payload handling code.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness allocates a small buffer based on the fuzz input, then calls [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_tcpip_rx`, which in turn calls `rx_icmp`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added includes for `<string.h>`, `<stddef.h>`, and `<stdint.h>`.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prefaced `rx_icmp` with multiple early‐exit checks:  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `pkt->ip != NULL`  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `pkt->raw.len` large enough for Ethernet+IP headers  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • IHL extracted from `pkt->ip->ver` is at least [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m, and full IP header fits in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `pkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` and destination IP matches interface  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Computed payload offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->pay.buf - raw.buf`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m lies within the raw buffer  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Clamped `pkt->pay.len` against transmit capacity  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If all checks pass, build an ICMP echo‐reply [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `tx_ip`, `memset`, `memcpy`, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ipcsum`, `ether_output`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch result  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After rebuilding and rerunning the same fuzz input, AddressSanitizer reports the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical heap‐buffer‐overflow in `rx_icmp` at the same code line.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer stack trace and shadow‐memory dump remain unchanged, indicating the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnew guards did not prevent the out‐of‐bounds read.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for further investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The relationship between `pkt->raw.buf`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`.len`, `pkt->pay.buf`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`.len`, and the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlayout of Ethernet, IP, and ICMP headers.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How `pkt` is initialized in the fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether `raw.len` and `pay.buf` are derived correctly.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The computation of header lengths [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`hlen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m versus the actual allocated [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->raw.len`.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Other protocol handlers in net_builtin.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., ARP, DHCP, TCP[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to ensure [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistent header‐parsing and bounds checks.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The implementation of `tx_ip` and how it uses `pkt->icmp` or buffer pointers, in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcase it relies on assumptions violated by malformed inputs.[0m                         [2m                [0m
